snippet.textDisplay: If you watched the Grammys, in lizzo’s acceptance speech she called for more music with meaning (or something like that lol), Demi belting her voice to an arena of people on national television after she had to restart with tears on her face is the type of power we need more of. & it’s why at the end she’s standing there nodding her head. Artists tell you how much pain goes into their work. Most of the greats are miserable & depressed with demons unimaginable. Regular people don’t understand how much this song hurts & HEALS simultaneously. If you watched this & didn’t shed a tear or two, you really DONT get it. This song wasn’t just for her. It was for everyone feeling the exact same way. She lived it & felt it & created it so SOMEONE doesn’t have to. Soulful.

snippet.textDisplay: I can relate to this song so deeply; minus the drugs/alcohol this is exactly how I felt when I was so depressed I then attempted to take my own life.. a few times. Mental health care is finally getting some respect from the populous.. I pray we can save our younger people from this pain and loneliness before it’s too late. Been in professional care for almost 12 years, I have a young child and my life is wonderful! I never would have made it without the right professional help. Nothing else worked for me. That’s why I want people to seek help and not just religion. God sent us guidance so use the tools please people. It works if you work it and it’s worth it.

Y’all do realize DEMI LOVATO DID NOT DO HEROIN?? Lmaooo Like I’m not quite understanding where y’all are getting that false information and why y’all are spreading that lie in the first place because if you look up what happened and what she overdosed in it was NOT heroin...

Like, you can literally look it up. “Law-enforcement sources initially told TMZ that Lovato overdosed on heroin, though a source close to Lovato later stated that was not the case. The singer has been open about struggling with cocaine and Oxycontin abuse in the past, and was reportedly treated at the scene with Narcan, which is an emergency medication used to reverse an opioid overdose. Her “friends” reportedly administered the medication themselves to revive her.”

snippet.textDisplay:
This song wrecked me. You have revealed the schism within my soul with this song Demi. I share in feeling this way so much toward others in my own way. For so long. With this song you bore so much of your own soul in, you spoke to me. I am LISTENING! I SEE YOU!

This song is a wonderful framework that can apply to so many from different struggles. I talk to my computer, I talk to my karaoke mic. I sing songs that mean the most to me. I don't have as much a tallent for written lyric. But even still, I feel no one is listening when I belt out a great rendition of Vicarious by Tool. Why isn't God helping the misled? America is in shambles. Everyone is falling apart but not listening. I just wish too there was someone, anyone, who would listen!

You broke my heart, and I love you now so much for it.

You put into words so much how I have been feeling. I could not have said anything better for this. Thank you.
Please, PLEASE stay here with us. I know this world is so dark. Possibly the darkest to ever exist. But our pain makes us seek light, by any means necessary. Your wonderful gift for music is your beacon and so many songs you have made come from a real place. Not just what might trend most. We need you on this planet. We need you. We need you.

snippet.textDisplay: 2019, my life felt like it was falling apart. I lost someone dear to me, my furry best friend of 13 years passed, I struggled with school, relationships became strained, and my depression was worse than it ever has been. I thought with the new year I would be able to move forward, but it’s proven to be difficult. A lot of Demi’s songs got me through a lot of life changing moments in my life. Her words and her messages comfort me in knowing that we all struggle and life can be tough but through music and each other we can find comfort. This song hit really hard but it was something that I really needed to hear, so thank you.
